radiographic_examinations.findings: No evidence of intracranial hemorrhage, mass, or acute territorial infarct; possible patchy hypoattenuation in the mesencephalon.

No acute intracranial or intraocular abnormality, no abnormal enhancement, no thrombosis of the dural venous sinuses or deep cerebral veins, and no hemodynamically significant stenosis, occlusion, or aneurysm. Mild dilatation of the superior ophthalmic veins that was greater on the right side.
